<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB08034</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT ESTABLISHING A STRATEGIC FOOD SECURITY RICE RESERVE AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Mandates the National Food Authority (NFA) to maintain rice reserve equivalent to fifteen (15) days of national rice consumption, buy stocks from small farmers and their cooperatives and import only under abnormal conditions, and release them to the market upon declaration of a state of calamity.
Strengthens farmers’ cooperatives by mandating the Cooperative Development Authority in coordination with the LGUs and NGOs to transform agri-based cooperatives into entrepreneurs. 
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ALIAS NAME : “Strategic Food Security Rice Reserve Act of 2018.”</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>ALEJANO, GARY C.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2018-08-06</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Bravo (M.) (000 2018-09-25)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON GOVERNMENT ENTERPRISES AND PRIVATIZATION ON 2018-10-10</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SECONDARILY REFERRED TO THE COMMITTEE(S) ON AGRICULTURE AND FOOD, FOOD SECURITY</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PREVIOUS COMMITTEE REFERRALS :PRIMARILY REFERRED TO FOOD SECURITY on 2018-08-08;</td></tr></table>